{{Infobox television |show_name = Crowned |image = Crowned Web Series Poster.jpg |genre = [[Comedy]] |creator = Josh Bednarsky, Brianne Sanborn |director = Josh Bednarsky |producer = [[Usher Morgan]] |starring = Brianne Sanborn, Veronica Mannion, Josh Bednarsky |country = United States |language = English |location = [[Los Angeles]], [[California]] |runtime = 5-10 minutes |network = [[YouTube]] |first_aired = {{Start date|2013|8|15}} |last_aired = present |website = http://www.crownedseries.com }}
'''''Crowned''''' is an [[United States|American]] [[comedy]] [[web series]] created by Josh Bednarsky and his wife Brianne Sanborn, who also wrote, directed and star in the episodes.<ref>https://www.imdb.com/title/tt2620136/</ref> The show follows Macie Edwards, an unemployed actress who, in a desperate effort to keep her apartment and pay her cat's medical bills takes a job as a [[Party Princess (Profession)|Party Princess]] in [[North Hollywood]], CA. The series depicts the everyday routine of party princesses in the fictional Crowned Entertainment Company. Most of the show follows a standard narrative style but often cuts to interviews with the employees of the fictional corporation to simulate the look of a documentary.<ref>http://sheltonherald.com/24502/crowned-series-hits-the-web24502/</ref>
==Premiere and Recognition==
The first episode premiered at a private event in [[Los Angeles, CA]]. The show became available on [[YouTube]] and the show's website on August 15, 2013, it became an instant [[viral video|hit]] online and some episodes surpassed 100,000 views.<ref>{{YouTube|g74VWlU4BOc}}</ref> The show's 2nd season has yet to be announced. [[Film Threat]] gave the show 3 out of 5 stars, film critic Mark Bell wrote "it’s an entertaining series, and it ends on a bit of a cliffhanger setting up some potentially fun dynamics for next season." <ref>http://www.filmthreat.com/reviews/72838/</ref>
==Production==
The series stars comedian [[Drew Droege]], [[Megan Heyn]] (Browsers, Freak Dance) and Veronica Mannion. The show was co-produced by [[Usher Morgan]] who also supervised the Post Production process. Before Morgan's involvement, the show had a successful [[Crowdfunding]] campaign and the producers raised the funds needed for [[principal photography]]. The series soundtrack includes songs from the British IBM.<ref>http://snobbyrobot.com/2013/07/16/crowned-being-a-princess-is-no-fairytale/</ref><ref>http://www.kicktraq.com/projects/joshbed/crowned-a-comedy-fantasy-web-series-about-princess/</ref><ref>http://shelton.patch.com/groups/arts-and-entertainment/p/crowned</ref>
