{{distinguish|Foo Fighters}} {{for|the TV cooking series|Food Fighters (TV series)}} {{notability|Products|date=February 2015}} '''Food Fighters''' was an [[action figure]] collection released by [[Mattel]] in 1989. [[Proverb]]ial for the concept of a [[food fight]], the figures were all different types of [[anthropomorphic]] food dressed in [[Military technology and equipment|military gear]]. Food Fighters consisted of ten figures and three accessory toys; a [[refrigerator]] [[playset]] was also designed but never produced. The characters were divided into two armies: the [[protagonist]] Kitchen Commandos and the [[antagonist]] Refrigerator Rejects.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Bellomo|first1=Mark|title=12 Toys From The 1980s That Didn't Take Off|url=http://mentalfloss.com/article/31875/12-toys-1980s-didnt-take|website=[[Mental Floss]]|accessdate=7 August 2015|date=12 December 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Galindo|first1=Brian|title=The Best Toy Line No One Remembers: "Food Fighters"|url=https://www.buzzfeed.com/briangalindo/the-best-toy-line-no-one-remembers-food-fighters|website=[[BuzzFeed]]|accessdate=7 August 2015|date=19 February 2013}}</ref> Each figure was made of a soft, hollow plastic similar to a [[squeaky toy]] and included a small hand weapon and removable backpack. The [[tagline]] on the figures' packaging read, "''Combat At Its Kookiest!''"
Food Fighters were commonly sold at small [[discount store]] chains like [[Hills Department Stores|Hills]] or [[Ben Franklin Stores|Ben Franklin]].
==Products== '''The Kitchen Commandos''' wore black boots, green clothing, and carried red weapons. * Burgerdier General, a [[hamburger]] * Colonel Pops, a box of [[popcorn]] * Major Munch, a [[doughnut]] (available with [[chocolate]] glaze or cherry glaze) * Lieutenant Legg, a [[Drumstick (poultry)#Cuts of poultry|chicken drumstick]] * Sergeant Scoop, an [[ice cream cone]] (available as chocolate and vanilla ice cream or [[sherbet (U.S.)|sherbet]]) * Corporal Crisp, a strip of [[bacon]] * Private Pizza, a slice of [[pepperoni]] and [[edible mushroom|mushroom]] [[pizza]] * The Combat Carton, an [[egg carton]] with a [[ketchup]] bottle [[cannon]] holding a tomato-slice missile on the top * The Fry Chopper, a [[frying pan]] [[helicopter]] with [[spatula]] blades * The Refrigerator playset, the Kitchen Commandos' base (unreleased)
'''The Refrigerator Rejects''' wore brown boots, black clothing, and carried blue weapons. * Mean Weener, a [[hot dog]] * Big Dumb Mis-Steak, a cut of [[ribeye steak]] * Chip the Ripper, a [[chocolate chip cookie]] (also available as a [[macadamia]] cookie) * Short Stack, a stack of [[pancakes]] (available with [[maple syrup]] or blueberry syrup) * Taco Terror, a [[taco]] * Rotten Egg Role, an [[egg roll]] * Fat Frenchy, a box of [[French fries]] * The BBQ Bomber, a [[grill (cooking)|barbecue grill]] armed with a spatula [[catapult]]
==See also== *[[Barnyard Commandos]]
